---
import GlobalLayout from '@/layouts/GlobalLayout.astro';
---

<GlobalLayout
  lang='en'
  title='Terms and Conditions'
  description='English "Terms and Conditions" page.'
>
  <div
    class='container mx-auto px-4 py-8 prose prose-sm sm:prose lg:prose-lg xl:prose-xl max-w-3xl'
  >
    <h1 class='text-3xl font-bold mb-6'>Terms and Conditions</h1>

    <p class='text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8'>
      Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US')}
    </p>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>1. The Company</h2>
      <p>Pixeau</p>
      <p>Chamber of Commerce (KvK) registration number: 95558667</p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>2. Applicability</h2>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        These Terms and Conditions shall apply to all offers made by Pixeau and
        to all agreements concluded between Pixeau and a User (hereinafter
        "User" or "You").
      </p>
      <p>
        The text of these Terms and Conditions shall be made available to the
        User prior to the conclusion of any agreement.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>3. The Offer</h2>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        If an offer has a limited duration or is subject to specific conditions,
        this shall be explicitly stated in the offer.
      </p>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        The offer shall contain a complete and accurate description of the
        products and/or services offered. The description shall be sufficiently
        detailed to enable a proper assessment of the offer by the User.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pixeau shall not be bound by manifest mistakes or errors in the offer.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>4. The Agreement</h2>
      <p>
        The agreement shall be concluded, subject to the provisions of [refer to
        relevant article, e.g., regarding acceptance], at the moment the User
        accepts the offer and complies with the conditions thereby set.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>
        5. Intellectual Property Rights
      </h2>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        All intellectual property rights relating to the materials (including
        but not limited to texts, images, and software) on this website are
        vested in Pixeau or its licensors.
      </p>
      <p>
        Copying, distribution, and any other use of these materials is
        prohibited without the prior written consent of Pixeau, except and only
        to the extent otherwise stipulated in regulations of mandatory law (such
        as the right to quote), unless otherwise indicated for specific
        materials.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>6. Liability</h2>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        Pixeau shall only be liable for direct damages. Any liability of Pixeau
        for indirect or consequential damages, including but not limited to loss
        of profit, missed savings, and damage due to business interruption, is
        excluded.
      </p>
      <p>
        The information on this website has been compiled with the utmost care.
        Nevertheless, Pixeau cannot guarantee that the information is complete,
        accurate, and/or current. No rights can be derived from the information
        on this website.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>7. Force Majeure</h2>
      <p>
        Pixeau shall not be obliged to fulfill any obligation towards the User
        if it is prevented from doing so as a result of a circumstance that is
        not attributable to its fault, and for which it is not accountable by
        virtue of law, a legal act, or generally accepted standards.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>
        8. Amendments to the Terms and Conditions
      </h2>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        Pixeau reserves the right to amend or supplement these Terms and
        Conditions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Minor amendments may be implemented at any time. Pixeau will endeavor to
        communicate significant substantive amendments to the User in advance.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>9. Governing Law and Disputes</h2>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        All legal relationships to which Pixeau is a party shall be governed
        exclusively by Dutch law.
      </p>
      <p>
        The court in Pixeau's place of business shall have exclusive
        jurisdiction to hear disputes, unless otherwise prescribed by mandatory
        law.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>10. Severability</h2>
      <p>
        If any provision of these Terms and Conditions is found to be void or
        unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and
        effect.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='mb-8'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-4'>11. Privacy Statement</h2>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        Pixeau respects the privacy of visitors to its website. We ensure that
        the personal information You provide to us is treated confidentially.
      </p>
      <p class='mb-2'>
        <strong>Cookies:</strong> Our website does not utilize first-party or third-party
        cookies that collect or store personally identifiable information for tracking
        purposes. Any cookies that may be used are strictly necessary for the technical
        operation of the website or for anonymous, aggregated statistical purposes
        to help us improve the website. As we do not use tracking cookies, we do
        not display a cookie banner.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</GlobalLayout>
